summary: The Vertiv™ NetSure™ Control Unit (NCU) includes models M830B and M830D.

The Vertiv™ NetSure™ Control Unit (NCU) enhances remote monitoring and control with a user-friendly interface, secure connectivity, advanced energy management features, and support for various communication protocols.

The NetSure Control Unit (NCU) is a versatile controller for DC power applications that enables remote monitoring and management of communication sites, offering features like intelligent load management, battery management, and compatibility with standard communication protocols.
The Vertiv™ NetSure™ Control Unit (NCU) is a management system designed to optimize and monitor power systems for enhanced efficiency and reliability.
The document outlines the technical specifications for a particular product or system.
The M830B model operates on a power supply of 19 VDC to 60 VDC with a maximum consumption of 18 W and a typical consumption of 4 W, while the specifications for the M830D are not provided.
The device operates within a temperature range of -20°C to +65°C (nominal) and -40°C to +75°C (extended), with a relative humidity tolerance of 0 to 90%.
The text outlines the compliance standards for safety, electromagnetic compatibility (EMC), and environmental requirements, including specific IEC, EN, UL, FCC, and NEBS certifications.
The text compares the dimensions, installation methods, and weight of two models, M830B and M830D, highlighting their differences in size and installation capabilities.

The M830B and M830D devices differ primarily in display resolution, communication capabilities, and input/output specifications, with the M830B featuring a lower resolution display and a wider range of analog inputs.
The text provides ordering information for two models of NCU3.0+ controllers, the M830B and M830D, differing in rack unit configurations.
The Optional Interface Board includes various configurations with relay outputs, digital inputs, DC voltages, currents, temperatures, and an additional Ethernet port.
